abstract: The couple met in 2012 while working on political campaigns, the bride for President Obama and the groom for Tim Kaine’s Senate bid.
snippet: The couple met in 2012 while working on political campaigns, the bride for President Obama and the groom for Tim Kaine’s Senate bid.
lead_paragraph: Elizabeth Bradstreet Foster and Tyrone Oliver Gayle were married May 5 at the Septenary Winery at Seven Oaks Farm in Charlottesville, Va. Senator Tim Kaine, Democrat of Virginia, officiated.

headline_main: California Today: Members of the Migrant Caravan Await Their Fate Near San Diego
byline_original: By Jose A. Del Real and Inyoung Kang

abstract: Thomas D. Homan, the agency’s acting director, faced opposition from several Senate Democrats — and even some Republicans — who said he was too aggressive in deporting undocumented immigrants.
snippet: Thomas D. Homan, the agency’s acting director, faced opposition from several Senate Democrats — and even some Republicans — who said he was too aggressive in deporting undocumented immigrants.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Thomas D. Homan, the acting director of Immigration and Customs Enforcement, said on Monday that he would retire from the deportation agency in June, after more than a year of pushing President Trump’s controversial plans to remove thousands of undocumented immigrants from the United States.

abstract: If you were to go into a lab and create a perfect candidate for 2020, it would be a big-hearted progressive whose appeal crossed class lines.
snippet: If you were to go into a lab and create a perfect candidate for 2020, it would be a big-hearted progressive whose appeal crossed class lines.
lead_paragraph: If the election were held today, Joe Biden would crush President Trump. Almost any other Democrat — including one named Generic Democrat — would also beat the man who runs an administration of kooks, quacks, criminals, drunks, wife beaters and grifters.

abstract: The 44 senators who questioned Mark Zuckerberg on Tuesday have one thing in common: They’re all his users.
snippet: The 44 senators who questioned Mark Zuckerberg on Tuesday have one thing in common: They’re all his users.
lead_paragraph: With respect to Facebook, United States senators don’t seem to be too different from many of us: They don’t necessarily trust it, but they’re not ready to quit it.
